messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /cms/user/captcha

- all HTTP methods acceptable: False

- HEAD: False

Explanation:
- The route is defined in app/api/cms/user.py as @user_api.route("/captcha", methods=["GET", "POST"]). That user blueprint is registered inside the cms blueprint with url_prefix="/user" (app/api/cms/__init__.py), and the cms blueprint is registered on the Flask app with url_prefix="/cms" (app/__init__.py). Combining these prefixes and the route path yields /cms/user/captcha.
- The accepted methods are determined strictly from the methods argument in the @route decorator in the provided code. Implicit framework behaviors (for example, frameworks sometimes providing HEAD when GET is present or automatic OPTIONS handling) were not assumed; only methods explicitly present in the source were considered.
